---
import ProjectCard from "./ProjectCard.astro";
---

<ProjectCard
  title="Firefly"
  shortDesc="A terminal music player with 4k lines of code."
  images={["projects/firefly_v0-7-0.gif", "projects/firefly_structure_1.png"]}
>
  <ul class="font-bold text-blue-400 list-disc list-inside">
    <li>First Commit: 2025-07-14 (Long-term Project)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Written in Rust, featuring <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://crates.io/crates/rodio"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">Rodio</a
    > (an audio playback library) and <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://ratatui.rs/"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">Ratatui</a
    > (a TUI framework).
    <br />
    This project involves multithreading, which exposes me to many new concepts,
    such as
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Atomic Reference Counted Pointer (Arc).</li>
      <li>Mutex (Lock) and lock poisoning.</li>
      <li>Communicating Sequential Processes (CSP) (mpsc channels in Rust).</li>
    </ul>

    It primarily supports FLAC, MP3, Opus, and WAV as of now. Other formats can
    still be used. Though, not by decoding directly but by temporarily
    converting the format to FLAC using <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://ffmpeg.org/"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">ffmpeg</a
    >, a multimedia framework.<br />

    I plan to continue to develop this app into something that can stand
    alongside popular music players like <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MusicBee"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">MusicBee</a
    >.
    <br />
  </p>

  <p>
    More detailed information and roadmap in
    <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://github.com/ilialyl/firefly"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Repository</a
    >.
  </p>
  <p>
    Try it on
    <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://github.com/ilialyl/firefly/releases/latest/download/firefly-x86_64-pc-windows-gnu.zip"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">Windows</a
    >
    or
    <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://github.com/ilialyl/firefly/releases/latest/download/firefly-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu.tar.gz"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">Linux</a
    >
    <br />
    <br />
  </p></ProjectCard
>
